[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(21) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "For Jozachar . . . smote him.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—Rather, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And Jozachar . . . it was that smote him.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " The names are different in Chronicles. (See the Note on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2Chronicles 24:26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".) Thenius notices the curious coincidence of the names as given here with the last words of the murdered Zechariah, “Jehovah see, and avenge!” The prophet was avenged by ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Jozachar",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (“Jehovah remembers”), the son of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "shimeath",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (“hearing”), and Jehozabad (“Jehovah bestows”), the son of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Shomer",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (“watcher”).",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "With his fathers—i.e., in the city of David; but “not in the sepulchres of the kings 2)” Chron. 24:25).",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "With his fathers",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "i.e.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", in the city of David; but “not in the sepulchres of the kings 2)” Chron. 24:25).",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
