  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "For Jozachar the son of Shimeath,.... Said to be an Ammonitess, and this man's name Zabad, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 24:26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and Jehozabad the son of Shomer, his servants; who is said in the same place to be the son of Shimrith a Moabitess: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "these smote him, and he died; justly did he fall by the hands of such persons for his idolatry: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and they buried him with his fathers in the city of David; but not in the sepulchres of the kings, because of his idolatry and murder of a priest of the Lord: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and Amaziah his son reigned in his stead; the conspirators not seeking the kingdom, but vengeance on him for his sins, which, whether right in them to do, was suffered by the Lord. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and Amaziah his son reigned in his stead; the conspirators not seeking the kingdom, but vengeance on him for his sins, which, whether right in them to do, was suffered by the Lord. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
